      <div>

<p>The Johnston typeface has undergone many changes since it was developed for London Underground by Edward Johnston in 1916.</p>
<p>TfL owns design and copyrights for all cuts of the Johnston 100 font. Application for a copy is only available by completing one of the licence request forms.</p>
<p>Johnston 100 was developed for use across our transport network. The Johnston Delf Smith typeface was developed for use on some historical signs.</p>
